801.text:
You can use the merchant password in the full game.

Say the password to the black market merchant hiding somewhere
in Kamurocho to do business with them and buy rare items.

803.text:
Look around the environment with the right stick.
If the Focus Icon appears, press the corresponding button to
focus on that point of interest, which may trigger an event.

805.text: ※You cannot use EXP to upgrade abilities in the demo.

806.text:
EXP is obtained by defeating enemies and clearing missions.
There are five types of EXP that apply to Kiryu's five skills.
You can also obtain EXP by eating.

808.text: ※You cannot use EXP to upgrade abilities in the demo.

809.text:
Eating at a restaurant recovers your health and gives you EXP.
Different foods generate different types of EXP.

Some menu combinations will even give you bonus EXP,
so try eating stuff that goes well together.

But remember, you won't gain any EXP if Kiryu is full.
Getting into fights is the best way to work up an appetite.

811.text:
Filling up your Heat Orbs enough will allow you to press R2
to enter Heat Mode. While in Extreme Heat Mode, Kiryu becomes
more powerful and can execute special Heat Action as well
as flurries of strikes. Use this to your advantage in tough fights.

813.text:
Eating will recover your health and a full meal will even
grant EXP. If you throw away or drop the food before
you've eaten it all, though, you won't recover health or
gain any EXP.

817.text:
Your progress is tracked through "Missions" which will
state your objective in the upper-right. This applies to
both main story objectives and substory objectives.
If you need to look at them again, you can find them
in the Pause Menu.

821.text: Convenience Stores are unavailable in the demo.
